Global Synthetic Food Antioxidants Market Insights
Synthetic Food Antioxidants Market size was valued at USD 2.1 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 4.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 10.1% from 2024 to 2030.

Synthetic Food Antioxidants Market Overview
The Synthetic Food Antioxidants market was valued at approximately USD 1.3 billion in 2023 and is projected to reach around USD 2.1 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.2% during the forecast period. The increasing demand for processed and packaged foods, coupled with the growing awareness of the health benefits of antioxidants, is driving market growth. Synthetic antioxidants, such as BHA, BHT, and TBHQ, are used extensively to prevent oxidative spoilage in foods, extending shelf life and maintaining quality. Their application spans a wide range of products, including snacks, oils, and convenience foods, contributing to the market’s growth. Additionally, the rise in demand for functional foods with enhanced nutritional profiles also propels the need for antioxidants in the food industry.

